programme.desc: Its a very merry Fieri holiday when Guy Fieris two sons and nephew face off in Flavortown. Guy pairs each family member with their very own All-Star chef partner, but he also gives each team a Secret Santa box full of weird ingredients to use.

programme.title: Barefoot Contessa
programme.desc: Ina assembles a gorgeous seasonal brunch. On the menu are morning glory muffins, a fresh fruit platter, shakshuka with feta, and a spicy bloody Mary.

programme.title: Barefoot Contessa
programme.desc: Ina creates a menu for a student entertaining blog site.

programme.title: Barefoot Contessa
programme.desc: Ina and her husband kick off the festive season with a getaway in the Berkshires with friends.

programme.title: Classic Mary Berry
programme.desc: Mary Berrys Christmas Party is the perfect invitation for Yuletide escape. Some of TVs best-loved faces join Mary to cook delicious dishes, especially for her Christmas Party.

programme.title: James Martin: Home Comforts at Christmas
programme.desc: James Martin gets ahead for Christmas, providing lots of clever tips and tricks to save time and stress on the big day. He is joined by Sir Michael Parkinson.

programme.title: James Martin: Home Comforts at Christmas
programme.desc: James Martin shows how to make impressive puds, Christmas Eve suppers and magnificent mains, and is joined by Helen Skelton.

programme.title: James Martin: Home Comforts at Christmas
programme.desc: James Martin brings together a classic collection of festive recipes to satisfy comfort food cravings. He is joined by Michel Roux Senior.

programme.title: James Martin: Home Comforts at Christmas
programme.desc: James Martin takes a trip down memory lane and recreates festive feasts inspired by his childhood. He is joined by racing driver Mark Webber.

programme.title: James Martin: Home Comforts at Christmas
programme.desc: James Martin uses the very best seasonal ingredients in fresh delicious dishes, from a mussel, pumpkin and saffron soup to a heart-warming Christmas casserole. He is joined by Charlie Dimmock.

programme.title: The Hairy Bikers: Mums Know Best
programme.desc: Si King and Dave Myers are on the search for the most interesting food that Britains mums are cooking for their families this Christmas. Si and Dave tour the nation hunting out Britains festive favourites and a few surprises. On their journey they find mums cooking everything from roast goose with all the trimmings to Pinnekjott and from festive gingerbread to Christmassy coconut samosas.

programme.title: Hairy Bikers At Christmas
programme.desc: The biking duo team up to throw an epic Christmas dinner for their combined families. They take a road trip along the Pennines in search of the best produce for their feast.

programme.title: The Hairy Bikers Twelve Days of Christmas
programme.desc: The Hairy Bikers journey through the verses of one of our most popular Christmas songs. For each line of the song, the boys have come up with a fantastic twist on a classic Christmas dish. From roast partridge with spiced pears (a partridge in a pear tree) and a classic trio of top end Poulets de Bresse chicken dishes (three French hens) to spiced Christmas pannacotta (eight Maids a-milking).

programme.title: The Hairy Bikers Christmas Party
programme.desc: Si King and Dave Myers are throwing a Christmas party for family, friends and some of the people they have met on the road over the last few years. However, this is a `hairy party so it will be anything but predictable. Its all about finger food, those tiny mouthfuls of loveliness that brighten up the festive season from the first Christmas party right through to New Years Eve.

programme.title: Michel Roux: Christmas In Provence
programme.desc: Michel cooks the best produce Southern France has to offer. Friends and family join the festivities as he serves up delicious Christmas dishes and the perfect festive drinks.

programme.title: Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives
programme.desc: This trip Guys chasing down the holiday meal every which way. In Portland, Maine, we visit a family-run joint where stuffed turkey and stuffed lobster are Thanksgiving traditions.

programme.title: Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives

programme.title: Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives
programme.desc: Guy Fieris loading up on things meaty, cheesy and a little sweet, like wild waffles in Anchorage, AK, and sizzlin steak tacos in Aspen, CO. Plus, in Albuquerque, NM, a lights-out Latin joint is going big with their amazing arepas and pork paninis.

programme.title: Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives
programme.desc: Guy Fieris getting cheesy and meaty, starting at a South Bound Brook, NJ, meat market stacking up their spin on the sloppy joe. In Nashville, a taco joint is piling nachos with local flavour; a down-home spot is serving the bomb barbecue pork mac.

programme.title: Life
programme.desc: An incredible look at birds reveals some of the extraordinary things that having feathers allows them to do. For the first time, a slow-motion camera captures the unique flight of the marvellous spatuletail hummingbird, and aerial photography takes us into the sky with an Ethiopian lammergeier. Also featured are the spectacular massed gathering of pink flamingoes, and the comic mating display of the sage grouse.

programme.title: Life
programme.desc: An incredible look at insects and how their armoured covering allowed them to become the most successful animal group ever. The camera flies with millions of monarch butterflies, while super slow motion shows a bombardier beetle firing boiling liquid at enemies through a rotating nozzle. Later, a honey bee army is seen stinging a raiding bear into submission, and a complex colony of grass cutter ants is seen like never before.

programme.title: Life
programme.desc: In the knife-edge world of hunters and hunted, mammals ability to learn new tricks is their key to survival. A killer whale is shown sneaking into a pool where elephant seal pups learn to swim, slow motion cameras reveal how the star-nosed mole can smell prey underwater, and young ibex demonstrate how to escape a fox by running up an almost vertical cliff face.

programme.title: Life
programme.desc: An investigation of marine invertebrates and the way they thrive in the toughest parts of the ocean. Divers swim into a shoal of predatory Humboldt squid as the creatures emerge from the depths to hunt in packs, time-lapse photography reveals thousands of starfish gathering under the Arctic ice to devour a seal carcass, and a giant octopus protects her eggs by using her body to wall up a cave, starving to death in the process.
